    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-03-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="649"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Sullivan</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 36.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-03-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 30, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Mr. Philip B. Livingston, the commercial agent of
                    the United States at Saint Andrews, represents that that island is quite
                    destitute of any government, and that the lives and property of citizens of the
                    United States have no protection. You will inquire into and report upon this
                    subject. It is particularly desirable to know whether any national interest of
                    the United States is endangered by the condition of affairs at the island as
                    represented.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peter</hi> J. <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan,</hi> Esq.,
                            <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
